=Episode 12=

17
00:01:55,248 --> 00:01:57,487
Can you guys adjust
the dough consistency for me?

18
00:01:58,008 --> 00:01:59,648
Make the dough a bit softer.

19
00:01:59,767 --> 00:02:01,648
Who makes steamed buns
with unleavened dough?

20
00:02:01,968 --> 00:02:02,767
Jiang Baichuan.

21
00:02:09,328 --> 00:02:10,648
Did Luo send you?

22
00:02:11,648 --> 00:02:13,048
She told you to hang on.

23
00:02:13,232 --> 00:02:14,832
South Mountain Hunters are working hard

24
00:02:14,832 --> 00:02:15,847
to come to rescue you.

25
00:02:15,847 --> 00:02:16,687
Don't come.

26
00:02:16,847 --> 00:02:17,528
Why?

27
00:02:18,287 --> 00:02:19,048
Tell them

28
00:02:19,088 --> 00:02:20,687
not to come to rescue me.

29
00:02:21,048 --> 00:02:22,088
Jiang, let me tell you.

30
00:02:22,208 --> 00:02:23,208
Those people

31
00:02:23,208 --> 00:02:24,447
would resort to any means.

32
00:02:24,968 --> 00:02:25,928
Then it means

33
00:02:25,928 --> 00:02:28,007
I have value to them

34
00:02:28,048 --> 00:02:29,928
and I can try
to extract some information.

35
00:02:30,368 --> 00:02:31,248
As long as I'm here,

36
00:02:31,407 --> 00:02:33,088
they'd think they have the upper hand

37
00:02:33,167 --> 00:02:34,287
and won't act recklessly.

38
00:02:34,368 --> 00:02:36,287
Luo and the others
will stay relatively safe.

39
00:02:37,007 --> 00:02:37,808
Are you sure?

40
00:02:37,887 --> 00:02:39,447
Of course.

41
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:42,088
Ask Luo to tell other Hunters

42
00:02:42,208 --> 00:02:43,488
to keep a close watch on Locust.

43
00:02:43,567 --> 00:02:45,007
It's not just a combat tool,

44
00:02:45,368 --> 00:02:46,167
but also a hostage.

45
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:47,847
Locust?

46
00:02:48,447 --> 00:02:50,048
I'm unfilial.

47
00:02:50,208 --> 00:02:51,007
Tell Luo

48
00:02:51,127 --> 00:02:52,368
not to worry about me.

49
00:02:52,368 --> 00:02:53,287
Take care of herself.

50
00:02:53,287 --> 00:02:55,407
That's what matters most to the Hunters.

51
00:02:55,507 --> 00:02:56,007
Leave.

52
00:02:56,007 --> 00:02:57,248
Okay.

53
00:03:22,847 --> 00:03:23,447
Hello.

54
00:03:28,328 --> 00:03:29,007
Hello.

55
00:03:29,928 --> 00:03:32,567
We've called him Jiang since childhood.

56
00:03:33,287 --> 00:03:34,127
So,

57
00:03:34,648 --> 00:03:35,687
I should call you...

58
00:03:35,687 --> 00:03:36,567
Just Quecha is fine.

59
00:03:47,127 --> 00:03:47,808
Yu Rong.

60
00:03:50,928 --> 00:03:52,287
I often heard Jiang mention you.

61
00:03:53,727 --> 00:03:55,048
Nothing good, I bet.

62
00:03:57,447 --> 00:03:58,248
Not at all.

63
00:03:59,407 --> 00:04:00,127
He said

64
00:04:01,328 --> 00:04:03,287
you've been taming beasts overseas.

65
00:04:04,127 --> 00:04:04,928
Taming beasts?

66
00:04:05,648 --> 00:04:06,607
He said that?

67
00:04:07,528 --> 00:04:08,248
Haven't you?

68
00:04:10,687 --> 00:04:11,368
He said

69
00:04:11,847 --> 00:04:14,567
you can't stand being constrained.

70
00:04:15,727 --> 00:04:17,568
But if the Hunters face real danger,

71
00:04:19,008 --> 00:04:20,487
he believes you'll definitely return.

72
00:04:22,088 --> 00:04:24,688
Indeed, he's right.

73
00:04:31,448 --> 00:04:32,607
I'm still too late.

74
00:04:37,088 --> 00:04:37,847
Sorry.

75
00:04:46,008 --> 00:04:48,208
An entire wild elephant herd,

76
00:04:48,648 --> 00:04:49,927
about ninety of them,

77
00:04:51,328 --> 00:04:53,047
escaped from the national park,

78
00:04:53,888 --> 00:04:55,727
and devoured farmers'

79
00:04:56,287 --> 00:04:57,047
rice crops

80
00:04:57,688 --> 00:04:58,727
and sugarcane.

81
00:04:59,487 --> 00:05:00,568
They even trampled roads

82
00:05:01,487 --> 00:05:02,727
and injured three people.

83
00:05:04,487 --> 00:05:06,047
I made tremendous effort

84
00:05:06,727 --> 00:05:08,407
to convince local authorities

85
00:05:08,927 --> 00:05:10,208
not to deploy the military,

86
00:05:11,287 --> 00:05:12,328
while herding them

87
00:05:12,807 --> 00:05:14,528
back into the national park.

88
00:05:15,927 --> 00:05:16,688
Impressive.

89
00:05:17,968 --> 00:05:19,247
No wonder Jiang said

90
00:05:19,607 --> 00:05:20,968
you're unruly,

91
00:05:22,008 --> 00:05:24,407
but you're the only one
worthy of Ghost Whip.

92
00:05:25,768 --> 00:05:26,927
Unruly?

93
00:05:27,367 --> 00:05:29,167
I got strictly trained.

94
00:05:30,968 --> 00:05:32,047
When I was young, Jiang

95
00:05:32,047 --> 00:05:34,247
always made me demonstrate for the boys.

96
00:05:48,688 --> 00:05:49,847
Can you teach me how?

97
00:05:52,448 --> 00:05:53,167
Teach what?

98
00:05:53,528 --> 00:05:54,407
Anything.

99
00:05:54,888 --> 00:05:56,208
As long as I can stay

100
00:05:58,008 --> 00:05:59,367
and help you.

101
00:06:46,568 --> 00:06:47,648
How did it feel when you

102
00:06:49,047 --> 00:06:50,208
first summoned the cauldron?

103
00:06:55,568 --> 00:06:56,847
Heavier than I expected.

104
00:07:04,807 --> 00:07:07,287
You shoulder heavy burdens as well.

105
00:07:10,088 --> 00:07:11,568
When Jiang summoned the cauldron,

106
00:07:12,927 --> 00:07:14,367
he made it look easy.

107
00:07:16,128 --> 00:07:17,088
Now I'm doing it myself,

108
00:07:19,208 --> 00:07:20,528
I realize it's not easy at all.

109
00:07:22,008 --> 00:07:25,927
You admit you were pretending it?

110
00:07:28,927 --> 00:07:29,528
Thank you

111
00:07:30,704 --> 00:07:32,088
for supporting me to keep Locust.

112
00:07:33,888 --> 00:07:35,807
You even gave it a name?

113
00:07:35,847 --> 00:07:37,688
You don't give the animals

114
00:07:38,247 --> 00:07:39,287
you care names?

115
00:07:43,927 --> 00:07:45,167
Supporting you

116
00:07:45,688 --> 00:07:47,247
doesn't mean I approve your approach.

117
00:07:47,727 --> 00:07:50,208
But there's no better option right now.

118
00:07:52,008 --> 00:07:53,888
Hope you won't change
your mind too quickly.

119
00:07:56,208 --> 00:07:58,528
I need to see it with my own eyes.

120
00:07:59,167 --> 00:08:00,847
I might regret it.

121
00:08:05,487 --> 00:08:06,088
Okay.

122
00:08:44,808 --> 00:08:45,887
Everything went smoothly?

123
00:08:48,127 --> 00:08:48,968
A few close calls.

124
00:08:50,048 --> 00:08:51,088
How are you feeling?

125
00:08:53,887 --> 00:08:54,487
I...

126
00:08:57,048 --> 00:08:57,968
I'm fine.

127
00:08:59,928 --> 00:09:00,647
Good then.

128
00:09:05,767 --> 00:09:06,688
Want to eat anything?

129
00:09:12,968 --> 00:09:14,048
I want to take a shower.

130
00:09:16,887 --> 00:09:18,048
Your wound can't get wet.

131
00:09:18,168 --> 00:09:19,487
Can I at least wash my hair?

132
00:10:08,367 --> 00:10:09,168
Don't...

133
00:10:09,767 --> 00:10:11,007
Don't worry too much.

134
00:10:12,007 --> 00:10:14,288
Jiang looks fine.

135
00:10:15,127 --> 00:10:16,808
And judging from where he's being held,

136
00:10:17,367 --> 00:10:19,367
Lin Xirou doesn't want
to harm him for now.

137
00:10:19,968 --> 00:10:22,168
Jiang also believes he's safe for now.

138
00:10:22,607 --> 00:10:24,767
So he told me to warn you
not to rescue him.

139
00:10:30,527 --> 00:10:31,408
Anyway,

140
00:10:31,568 --> 00:10:32,887
focus on recovering first.

141
00:10:42,328 --> 00:10:42,887
Right.

142
00:10:43,247 --> 00:10:44,408
Jiang also told you

143
00:10:45,328 --> 00:10:46,767
to keep a close eye on that...

144
00:10:48,887 --> 00:10:49,847
What's that again?

145
00:10:51,127 --> 00:10:51,808
Keep a close eye

146
00:10:52,968 --> 00:10:54,568
on Locust. Right, Locust.

147
00:10:55,208 --> 00:10:58,208
He said it's both a tool and a hostage.

148
00:11:01,647 --> 00:11:02,887
Who is Locust?

149
00:11:03,647 --> 00:11:05,088
What else did he tell you?

150
00:11:06,767 --> 00:11:07,727
Nothing else.

151
00:11:08,168 --> 00:11:10,088
We didn't have time to talk more.

152
00:11:14,568 --> 00:11:16,247
Alright, sit up.

153
00:11:41,208 --> 00:11:42,727
You can return Mr. Changxi's phone

154
00:11:42,727 --> 00:11:43,408
to him.

155
00:11:43,408 --> 00:11:44,048
It's fixed.

156
00:12:00,688 --> 00:12:01,288
Thanks.

157
00:12:03,208 --> 00:12:04,968
In case you get bored,

158
00:12:05,127 --> 00:12:07,088
I prepared some clay

159
00:12:07,328 --> 00:12:09,007
and sculpting tools for you.

160
00:12:09,007 --> 00:12:10,247
Not sure if you'll need them.

161
00:12:12,048 --> 00:12:13,088
Guess I'll have

162
00:12:13,088 --> 00:12:13,968
to sculpt

163
00:12:13,968 --> 00:12:15,048
after my arm heals.

164
00:12:17,607 --> 00:12:18,288
Right.

165
00:12:19,568 --> 00:12:20,247
Makes sense.

166
00:12:23,288 --> 00:12:23,968
It's okay.

167
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:26,727
I also brought you some books.

168
00:12:27,607 --> 00:12:29,448
If you can't sculpt,
you can at least read.

169
00:12:30,487 --> 00:12:31,168
Here they are.

170
00:12:52,568 --> 00:12:53,367
This...

171
00:12:55,527 --> 00:12:57,208
Are you trying to entertain me

172
00:12:57,607 --> 00:12:59,208
or force me into seclusion for creation?

173
00:12:59,568 --> 00:13:01,168
You're like my agent.

174
00:13:16,487 --> 00:13:17,168
And this.

175
00:13:17,887 --> 00:13:18,767
I cleaned it for you.

176
00:13:36,767 --> 00:13:38,647
I feel the most secure
when it's in my hand.

177
00:13:43,688 --> 00:13:45,847
Is this the Mad Blade?

178
00:14:19,688 --> 00:14:20,887
It seems scared.

179
00:14:22,247 --> 00:14:23,808
I thought it's already tamed?

180
00:14:25,328 --> 00:14:26,448
Why still scared of people?

181
00:14:26,808 --> 00:14:29,887
Maybe because Ghost Whip is here.

182
00:14:33,887 --> 00:14:35,448
Such a large living Earth Fiend.

183
00:14:36,448 --> 00:14:37,607
If it doesn't run,

184
00:14:38,288 --> 00:14:40,607
how long will you keep hiding it?

185
00:14:45,568 --> 00:14:46,247
Jiang said it was

186
00:14:46,247 --> 00:14:48,328
captured during a mountain patrol
twenty years ago.

187
00:14:49,247 --> 00:14:50,607
That year the Mad Blade died.

188
00:14:51,568 --> 00:14:52,928
Golden Gate's being repaired.

189
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:56,847
We couldn't kill it or release it,

190
00:14:57,928 --> 00:14:58,887
so had to keep it here.

191
00:15:00,448 --> 00:15:01,288
What happened next?

192
00:15:01,887 --> 00:15:04,007
One year, I and two Hound kids
were told to go

193
00:15:04,408 --> 00:15:05,367
for mountain training,

194
00:15:06,448 --> 00:15:08,367
but we loafed around
and wanted to roast locusts.

195
00:15:09,487 --> 00:15:10,607
Just as we lit the fire,

196
00:15:11,647 --> 00:15:13,208
Mr. Crip caught us red-handed.

197
00:15:15,127 --> 00:15:17,847
He locked us in the septic tank
behind the mountain.

198
00:15:18,247 --> 00:15:19,527
We Hounds couldn't

199
00:15:19,968 --> 00:15:21,408
tolerate that stench overnight.

200
00:15:22,527 --> 00:15:23,288
At midnight,

201
00:15:24,448 --> 00:15:26,247
we picked the lock and escaped.

202
00:15:27,527 --> 00:15:28,808
But I got lost

203
00:15:30,487 --> 00:15:31,408
and discovered it

204
00:15:32,847 --> 00:15:34,088
in this place.

205
00:15:38,527 --> 00:15:39,727
Now that you mention it,

206
00:15:39,847 --> 00:15:40,847
I remember

207
00:15:41,928 --> 00:15:44,968
you guys were punished
to clean the toilet for three more days,

208
00:15:45,727 --> 00:15:46,408
right?

209
00:15:50,808 --> 00:15:52,527
So since then,

210
00:15:53,127 --> 00:15:54,367
you've been taming it?

211
00:15:57,048 --> 00:15:57,767
No.

212
00:15:59,568 --> 00:16:01,288
After you guys left one by one,

213
00:16:02,568 --> 00:16:04,688
only Ma Hanzi and I stayed behind.

214
00:16:06,448 --> 00:16:08,647
So Jiang entrusted it to me.

215
00:16:11,328 --> 00:16:12,727
Maybe to you,

216
00:16:13,168 --> 00:16:14,088
it's an old friend.

217
00:16:15,048 --> 00:16:17,127
But to other South Mountain Hunters,

218
00:16:18,448 --> 00:16:19,487
it's an enemy.

219
00:16:22,088 --> 00:16:24,448
I wanted to turn enemy into friend,

220
00:16:25,527 --> 00:16:26,607
and then defeat it.

221
00:16:28,847 --> 00:16:30,527
Before, you were just on your own.

222
00:16:31,208 --> 00:16:32,607
Now you are the leader.

223
00:16:35,688 --> 00:16:37,527
I hope you can tell

224
00:16:39,048 --> 00:16:40,288
friend from enemy.

225
00:16:42,887 --> 00:16:43,808
Since you're here,

226
00:16:45,968 --> 00:16:47,727
let's visit another person

227
00:16:48,928 --> 00:16:50,328
who can't tell friend from enemy.

228
00:17:00,887 --> 00:17:04,007
So Ms. Lin doesn't
give birth to any kids?

229
00:17:04,968 --> 00:17:05,608
No.

230
00:17:07,688 --> 00:17:09,327
When were you adopted then?

231
00:17:11,727 --> 00:17:13,007
Must we talk about this?

232
00:17:17,608 --> 00:17:19,487
You agreed to come out today

233
00:17:19,968 --> 00:17:21,487
just as a formality.

234
00:17:21,527 --> 00:17:22,368
I know it.

235
00:17:23,368 --> 00:17:24,527
But think carefully.

236
00:17:24,888 --> 00:17:25,888
If she asks me

237
00:17:25,888 --> 00:17:27,448
what we talked about,

238
00:17:27,928 --> 00:17:29,368
I can't just tell her nothing.

239
00:17:31,688 --> 00:17:34,007
Then change the subject.

240
00:17:39,007 --> 00:17:39,608
Got it.

241
00:17:40,287 --> 00:17:42,287
I'll start with myself

242
00:17:42,688 --> 00:17:43,888
to break the ice.

243
00:17:46,648 --> 00:17:47,888
I'm also an orphan,

244
00:17:48,128 --> 00:17:49,408
but no one adopted me.

245
00:17:49,767 --> 00:17:51,247
I grew up in a welfare home.

246
00:17:53,767 --> 00:17:56,767
I only knew Ms. Lin sponsored you.

247
00:17:58,567 --> 00:18:01,247
When I was young,
the welfare home reformed.

248
00:18:01,608 --> 00:18:03,327
They stopped annual visits

249
00:18:03,327 --> 00:18:04,608
and superficial formalities,

250
00:18:04,968 --> 00:18:06,327
but host a sponsorship program.

251
00:18:06,848 --> 00:18:09,168
Any business or individual

252
00:18:09,448 --> 00:18:11,368
could choose a child to sponsor,

253
00:18:11,727 --> 00:18:13,848
covering their education

254
00:18:13,968 --> 00:18:14,848
and living costs.

255
00:18:15,527 --> 00:18:18,087
I was lucky to be chosen by Roadsound.

256
00:18:18,688 --> 00:18:20,608
Ms. Lin never even met us,

257
00:18:21,208 --> 00:18:23,767
but fully sponsored three kids at once.

258
00:18:26,727 --> 00:18:27,688
To tell the truth,

259
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:29,567
among the three of us,

260
00:18:31,287 --> 00:18:33,487
one now works
in telecommunications abroad,

261
00:18:34,208 --> 00:18:36,007
another does research at Roadsound,

262
00:18:37,487 --> 00:18:40,168
and I'm the unpromising one,
just self-employed.

263
00:18:43,767 --> 00:18:47,287
Actually, Ms. Lin often praises you.

264
00:18:49,007 --> 00:18:49,767
Is that so?

265
00:18:51,168 --> 00:18:53,287
That's why I call Ms. Lin my benefactor.

266
00:18:55,168 --> 00:18:56,928
Now she's even introduced you to me.

267
00:18:57,327 --> 00:18:59,327
Not sure why I'm that lucky.

268
00:19:00,608 --> 00:19:01,208
Let's go.

269
00:19:04,688 --> 00:19:05,287
Go.

270
00:19:08,287 --> 00:19:09,047
Be careful.

271
00:19:09,767 --> 00:19:10,368
Be careful.

272
00:19:22,368 --> 00:19:22,968
What's wrong?

273
00:19:27,087 --> 00:19:27,888
N-Nothing.

274
00:19:28,807 --> 00:19:29,448
Let's go.

275
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:33,287
A stall selling
qingtuan rice balls ahead.

276
00:19:33,527 --> 00:19:34,327
Ever tried it?

277
00:19:34,807 --> 00:19:35,408
No.

278
00:19:35,487 --> 00:19:36,087
Let's go.

279
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:42,224
(Luo)

280
00:19:43,727 --> 00:19:44,327
Sorry.

281
00:19:44,327 --> 00:19:46,608
I failed to notify you
that mission's canceled.

282
00:19:46,608 --> 00:19:47,408
No need to worry.

283
00:19:49,287 --> 00:19:49,888
Sorry.

284
00:19:49,888 --> 00:19:52,168
I failed to notify you
that mission's canceled.

285
00:19:52,168 --> 00:19:52,968
No need to worry.

286
00:19:56,287 --> 00:19:58,287
Is he completely dead?

287
00:19:58,848 --> 00:20:00,408
The skull apex and the seventh vertebra

